<item>
            <title>[LU-20045] l_getsepol fails to find SELinux policy on REHL10.1</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20045</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;l_getsepol&lt;/tt&gt; calls &lt;tt&gt;security_policyvers()&lt;/tt&gt;, which returns version &lt;b&gt;33&lt;/b&gt;. However, RHEL 10.1 uses policy version &lt;b&gt;35&lt;/b&gt; (located at &lt;tt&gt;/etc/selinux/targeted/policy/policy.35&lt;/tt&gt;). Because &lt;tt&gt;l_getsepol&lt;/tt&gt; searches downward from the returned version (33, 32, 31...), it fails to find the actual policy file.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>RHEL10.1 with Lustre client installed</environment>
        <key id="96603">LU-20045</key>
